            "answer_text": "It\u2019s my understanding if someone is of legal age and they can pass a background check there is nothing preventing them from buying a firearm. If they still live at home and their parents don\u2019t want it in the house that is a completely different issue. I watched a episode of Live PD a while back where a landlord called the police on a tenant because the tenant was a gun collector and had several in the home. The landlord was an anti-gun nut and wanted the guns out of the house and called the police. The police arrived and said there was nothing they could do as the tenant had the right to own them, was being responsible by keeping them secured and was not breaking any laws. Despite what the landlord had stated in the lease the police could do nothing about it. So it became a civil dispute. The same thing would happen between an adult child and the parents. ",
