            },
            "answer_text": "Yes and NO. IF the child is an adult and can pass the BG checks, no they cant stop the child from buying a gun. They can tell the adult child they can live there but no guns because its their house and their rules. . BUT there is a grey area. IF the child is paying rent like a tenant/landlord then no the parent cannot prevent the child from bringing any legal product into their home. So they would be playing with the constitutional rights of the child. No different then if they banned the child from voting. they cannot stop a legal adult child from owning a gun but they can ask the child to move out if they want to own that gun. Now if the child was acting badly and threatening to harm themselves or others the parents can contact lawenforcement to deal with it. ",
