            "answer_text": "If the adult can legally buy a firearm so generally 18 for a rifle/shotgun and 21 for a handgun, some states are also 21 for a rifle/shotgun ad pass the background check there is nothing the parents can do to prevent buying and owning. Now talking about where it is kept is a different thing, it might not always hold up in court but the way it generally works is they're house their rules. It could be treated as a civil matter if this adult that is still living at home wants to keep them there. ",
