                "name": "Frank Williams, Jr.",
                "href": "/profile/Frank-Williams-Jr-4"
            },
            "answer_text": "You would only have two options here: Refuse to allow the firearm in your house. You can't legally stop them from owning it, but you can legally stop them from bringing it on your property.Refuse to let them continue to live there if they wish to own firearms. This is really just a more extreme version of option 1.If, for so.e reason, your child is mentally incapable of taking care of themself then you might be able to go through the court system and have them legally declared so. That would remove their ability to legally possess firearms for a while (forever if they can't convince a court that they are, in fact, mentally competent). ",
